        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 2:23PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 223 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hume, or 12 miles southwest of Rich Hill, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Richards, Deerfield, Metz, Stotesbury, and Horton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
